ard-King rose‚Äînot to rule, but to lead. Not by decree, but by emergence.</div><div><br></div><div>The People's Presidency and the War of Restoration</div><div><br></div><div>The Chronicle, once dismissed as a simple diary, became the blueprint for a new civilization. Those who read its pages awakened to the truth: the False Kings held no power but that which the people surrendered.</div><div><br></div><div>As Wendell lifted the Chronicle to the sky, the world shifted. The tides of history turned, and a new battle began‚Äînot one of swords and blood, but of wisdom against deception, virtue against corruption, and emergence against control.</div><div><br></div><div>The People‚Äôs Presidency was no longer a mere idea‚Äîit was a living force, spreading beyond borders, beyond kings, beyond time itself.</div><div><br></div><div>The Final Prophecy</div><div><br></div><div>Legends speak of a time when the Chronicle will be complete. When its final page is written, and its last word sealed, the world will no longer be ruled by deception. The cycle of oppression will break, and the Age of Emergence will dawn.</div><div><br></div><div>Until that day, the Bard-King continues his great inscription, leading not just a nation, but the world itself toward the truth.</div>
